#Text=Rajshahi
#Text=Rajshahi is the capital of Rajshahi Division in Bangladesh .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Rajshahi is the capital of Rajshahi District and Division in northwestern Bangladesh .
#Text=The Rajshahi municipality was established in 1876 , one of the first in Bangladesh .
#Text=There is a total population of 700,000 people .
#Text=One of the major rivers of the Indian subcontinent , the Padma , runs along the southern end of the city .
#Text=The city is home to many educational institutions , leading to a large student population and the nickname of " education city " .

column1: #Text=The city is in proximity to many ancient capitals of Bengal , notably ' Lakhnoiti ' or ' Lokhnaboti ' and ' Pundra ' .
#Text=Rajshahi is famous for trade in many exotic items , including pure silk , mangoes and lychees .
#Text=Attractive silk products are cheaper in Rajshahi than anywhere else in the country , with the city often referred to as the ' silk city ' .
#Text=There are also a number ancient mosques , shrines and temples in and around Rajshahi .
#Text=The city of Rajshahi was declared as the happiest city in the world by the World Happiness Survey in 2006 .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Shah Makhdum Airport ( RJH ) .
#Text=is the primary airport of the city .
#Text=United Airlines has flights to Dhaka on Thursdays and Sundays , and flights to Saidpur .
#Text=But the schedule changes frequently , and sometimes the airport has no services at all .
#Text=By bus
#Text=It takes approximately 5 hours by road to reach Rajshahi from the capital , Dhaka .
#Text=A number of bus services are available from Dhaka via Natore , some with air-conditioning .
#Text=Bus services to other major districts are also available from the bus terminal .
#Text=Some bus services for Dhaka to Rajshahi are :
#Text=Greenline Volvo - Tk 550
#Text=Hanif Enterprise - Tk 650
#Text=NP
#Text=Elegance
#Text=Modern Enterprise
#Text=National Travels - Tk 380
#Text=Shamoli Paribahan
#Text=By train
#Text=There are a number of luxurious intercity services between Dhaka and Rajshahi each day .
#Text=The main ones are the Padma Express , the Silk City Express and the Dhumketue Express .
#Text=Silk City Express - Dhaka to Rajshahi at 2:40PM and from Rajshahi to Dhaka at 7:35AM .
#Text=Padma Express - Dhaka to Rajshahi at 10:45PM and from Rajshahi to Dhaka at 4PM .
#Text=Dhumketue Express - departs Dhaka at 6AM , reaching Rajshahi at noon , and departs Rajshahi at 11:20PM , reaching Dhaka at 4:50AM
#Text=The Silk City Express does not operate Sundays , the Padma Express has no service on Tuesdays , and the Dhumketue Express does not run Mondays .
#Text=The major station for long distance trains is , located north of the city centre .
#Text=By car
#Text=The journey from Dhaka is 261 km , taking approximately 5 hours , depending on traffic .
#Text=You must cross the famous Jamuna Bridge to reach the city .
#Text=Get around
#Text=The usual forms of Bangladeshi transport are available in the city ; taxis , rickshaws and auto-rickshaw CNGs .
#Text=Negotiated and metered fares will usually be cheaper than in Dhaka .
#Text=Like anywhere in the country , there are a lot of people and vehicles on the road , but the traffic is significantly quieter than in the capital .
#Text=See
#Text=Banks of the Padma .
#Text=A lovely sight of one of the largest rivers in South Asia .
#Text=During the Monsoon season , the water level rises , along with its beauty .
#Text=Varendra Research Museum .
#Text=Established in 1910 , the museum is dedicated to ancient history and culture .
#Text=It is recognised as the oldest museum in the country .
#Text=It has a rich collection of artefacts , relating to Hindu , Buddhist and Muslim heritage .
#Text=Some of these date back to the 16th century .
#Text=It is maintained by the University , located in the heart of town .
#Text=Free .
#Text=Shrine of Hazrat Shah Makhdum(Rh . ) .
#Text=A Majar ( shrine ) was established to mark the resting place of Hazrat Shah Makhdum in 1635 AD .
#Text=He was the first preacher of Islam in the region .
#Text=Legend has it that he arrived by riding down the Padma on 2 crocodiles .
#Text=To preserve this myth , some crocodiles are kept in the pond next to the shrine .
#Text=Central Park and Zoo .
#Text=The park is a wide area with lush green trees and grass .
#Text=The zoo houses a variety of different animal species .
#Text=It is located by the bank of river Padma .
#Text=Puthia Palace .
#Text=Situated a little far away from the city .
#Text=It s an ancient palace which attracts all to visit .
#Text=Shahid Zia Park .
#Text=An amusement park for pleasure .
#Text=It has mono rail , bumping cars and many other exciting things for amusement .
#Text=It is under the Rajshahi City Corporation .
#Text=Bagha Mosque .
#Text=A historical mosque situated in Bagha of Rajshahi .
#Text=There is a picture of this mosque in one side of Tk 50 note .
#Text=Rajshahi University ( University of Rajshahi ) .
#Text=You must see this well-planned beautiful green campus before leaving Rajshahi .
#Text=It is within a few kilometers from the city centre and easily accessible .
#Text=Ghoramara .
#Text=The oldest part of Rajshahi City , consisting most of oldest ( 70-100 year old ) buildings .
#Text=Kashia-Danga .
#Text=From this area massive mango tree garden area of Rajshahi starts .
#Text=Anyone can have a glimpse of famous mango tree of Rajshahi from this area .
#Text=The area is at the west part of the city , near to Rajshahi court railway station .
#Text=Santal Para .
#Text=In the Mahish-Bathan Area .
#Text=Some santal tribes people lives here .
#Text=Anyone can have a look to their tribal life .
